{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Local dev / agent clone identity setup + docs\n\nEach human/agent clone writes non-exempt tickets and needs its OWN identity (not the bot).\n\n- Document the setup in `docs/identity.md` / `docs/local-dev-env.md`: create/own an identity ticket, `rebar identity use <id>` (writes git-ignored `.rebar/current_identity`), and set `identity.signing_key` (or export `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`) to the developer's local SSH private key under `~/.ssh/`.\n- Note the `git config user.email` fallback resolution path.\n- Make explicit that the signing key is per-machine and never committed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `docs/identity.md` (and/or `docs/local-dev-env.md`) documents the per-clone identity + signing-key setup and the git-email fallback.\n- [ ] A local clone following the docs produces a signed write, verifiable via `rebar show <id>` (the written event shows `authorship.signed ≥ 1`) and/or `rebar verify-authorship` emitting a `verified` verdict for it. (NOT `verify-signature`, which certifies HMAC manifest attestations from the `rebar sign` flow, not SSH-based event authorship.)\n- [ ] Docs state the key is per-machine and uncommitted."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784002128500593001,"uuid":"cc5844d0-3438-48a7-aa10-f73a2c331372"}